abstract: As Democrats gather for the next presidential debates this week, several are struggling with fund-raising. An accounting maneuver last month made some appear to have more cash on hand than they did.
snippet: As Democrats gather for the next presidential debates this week, several are struggling with fund-raising. An accounting maneuver last month made some appear to have more cash on hand than they did.
lead_paragraph: Staff members for a half dozen Democratic presidential candidates did not receive their final June paycheck that month. Instead, their campaigns nudged payday into July, an accounting maneuver that obscured payroll costs and temporarily made it look like candidates had more cash on hand than they actually did.

abstract: In a key swing state, Democrats looking at the presidential field were more likely to follow their head than their heart in whom to support.
snippet: In a key swing state, Democrats looking at the presidential field were more likely to follow their head than their heart in whom to support.
lead_paragraph: NEWTOWN, Pa. — Diane LeBas, a 71-year-old substitute teacher attending the Newtown Democrats’ summer picnic on Sunday, recounted how she was tear-gassed protesting the Vietnam War. No one could question her progressivism.

abstract: For half of the candidates, it may be their last chance to make an impression on the national debate stage.
snippet: For half of the candidates, it may be their last chance to make an impression on the national debate stage.
lead_paragraph: When 20 Democratic presidential candidates gather for the second round of debates this Tuesday and Wednesday, about half of them will do so with the understanding that it will probably be their last time debating on the national stage this election cycle.

abstract: Prosecutors can’t be truly independent. We can.
snippet: Prosecutors can’t be truly independent. We can.
lead_paragraph: After a police officer in South Bend, Ind., shot and killed Eric Jack Logan last month, contentious meetings between the public and Mayor Pete Buttigieg showed that there is often a serious lack of faith that allegations of police misconduct will be fairly investigated. We can fix this: Public defenders, not law enforcement officials, should be responsible for determining whether police misconduct occurred.
